# Deterministic component viewport

## Goal

Give every mounted component a deterministic viewport measured in DF cells.
Tests can select the viewport while mounting a component and can change it
later through `ds.viewport(...)`. Widgets, overlays, and complete screens must
all observe the same mount-owned dimensions.

The work is complete when viewport behavior is consistent across all supported
component categories, documented for test authors, covered by offline unit
tests, and proven by the applicable live DFHack specifications.

## Decisions

- [x] Continue using `viewport` as the public and internal term.
- [x] Express viewport dimensions in DF cells, not pixels.
- [x] Keep the mount option shape
  `viewport={width=<positive integer>, height=<positive integer>}`.
- [x] Use `{width=128, height=64}` as the default viewport, approximating a
  1024 by 768 display when cells are 8 by 12 pixels.
- [x] Rename the runtime command from `ds.resize(...)` to `ds.viewport(...)`.
- [x] Remove `ds.resize(...)` instead of retaining a compatibility alias while
  DwarfSpec is pre-1.0.
- [x] Keep live DFHack specifications out of GitHub CI; CI runs only offline
  unit, syntax, packaging, and publication checks.

## Public contract

- [ ] Document `ds.mount(component, {viewport={width, height}})` with the
  default and explicit-override behavior.
- [ ] Define `ds.viewport(width, height)` as a command on the implicit current
  mount.
- [ ] Require positive integer width and height values for both entry points.
- [ ] Make `ds.viewport(...)` fail with the standard missing-current-mount
  diagnostic when no component is mounted.
- [ ] Make `ds.viewport(...)` wait for the render caused by the viewport
  change before returning.
- [ ] Confirm that a new mount starts from its requested viewport or the
  default and never inherits dimensions from an earlier mount.

## Component boundary and mount state

- [ ] Change viewport normalization so an omitted value produces a fresh
  `{width=128, height=64}` table.
- [ ] Preserve viewport as a mount-only option rather than forwarding it as a
  component constructor attribute.
- [ ] Store the normalized viewport as mutable state owned by the mount.
- [ ] Ensure caller-owned viewport tables cannot be mutated by runtime viewport
  changes.
- [ ] Add a mount-context operation that validates and applies new dimensions
  through the active component adapter.
- [ ] Route failures through existing mount diagnostics and cleanup ownership.

## Adapter behavior

- [ ] Define an adapter viewport-update contract shared by widgets, overlays,
  and complete screens.
- [ ] Update the DwarfSpec widget host viewport before invoking its resize and
  layout behavior.
- [ ] Make ordinary widget layout use the current mount-owned viewport.
- [ ] Make overlay layout and painter rectangles use the current mount-owned
  viewport.
- [ ] Verify both fullscreen and scaled-interface overlay painter paths after a
  runtime viewport change.
- [ ] Make complete-screen resize interception read the current mutable
  viewport instead of dimensions captured during mounting.
- [ ] Preserve reversible instance interception for complete screens.
- [ ] Preserve existing render instrumentation, backing viewscreen, pause, and
  cleanup behavior for every adapter.

## API migration

- [ ] Export `ds.viewport(width, height)` from the live interaction namespace.
- [ ] Remove `ds.resize(width, height)` from the exported API.
- [ ] Replace every DwarfSpec specification call to `ds.resize(...)` with
  `ds.viewport(...)`.
- [ ] Update API export assertions for the renamed command.
- [ ] Search source, tests, examples, and active documentation for stale
  `ds.resize` references.

## Offline unit coverage

- [ ] Prove that omitted mount options normalize to `{width=128, height=64}`.
- [ ] Prove that explicit viewport dimensions override the default.
- [ ] Prove rejection of missing, fractional, zero, negative, and nonnumeric
  dimensions where applicable.
- [ ] Prove that normalization copies caller-owned viewport tables.
- [ ] Prove default and explicit widget-host layout dimensions.
- [ ] Prove runtime widget viewport changes and repeated changes.
- [ ] Prove overlay layout and painter dimensions follow runtime changes.
- [ ] Prove complete screens follow runtime changes while their original
  resize method remains recoverable.
- [ ] Prove viewport state is isolated between sequential mounts.
- [ ] Prove unmount and failed-mount cleanup restore all intercepted methods and
  leave no active mount resources.

## Live DFHack proof

- [ ] Prove an ordinary widget receives the default viewport on its first
  completed render.
- [ ] Prove an ordinary widget receives an explicit mount-time viewport.
- [ ] Prove `ds.viewport(...)` changes an ordinary widget's live parent frame.
- [ ] Prove an overlay receives matching layout and painter dimensions at mount
  time and after a runtime change.
- [ ] Prove a complete screen receives default, explicit, and runtime viewport
  dimensions without replacing its native behavior permanently.
- [ ] Prove cleanup after each live case leaves no active DwarfSpec-owned
  screen, subject, or interception.
- [ ] Record live proof separately from offline CI results.

## Documentation and release checks

- [ ] Update the command table and authoring examples to use `ds.viewport(...)`.
- [ ] Explain that viewport dimensions are DF cells and document the 128 by 64
  default and its 8 by 12 cell assumption.
- [ ] Update architecture documentation to describe mutable mount-owned
  viewport state and adapter propagation.
- [ ] Add an entry to the changelog describing the deterministic default and
  command rename.
- [ ] Run the full offline Busted suite.
- [ ] Run Lua syntax and formatting checks.
- [ ] Run package verification and confirm the LuaRock includes updated source
  and documentation.
- [ ] Run `git diff --check` and review the final diff for unrelated changes.
